title: Improve handling erros in Network (repeat also ClientError.SOCKET errors)
message:
Improve handling erros in Network (repeat also ClientError.SOCKET errors)

Previously it tried again only when server return empty string, now it takes care also of special client errors (only socket problems right now) which are solvable simply by repeating the request.

I also raised the number of retries to 3, which allows cases where server return "" -> so we do request again -> now we've got socket error -> so now we finally try again for last time.

Merge branch 'robyer/tasks-improvements'

Complete refactoring of using tasks. Provides much more automatic behavior and new functions (like scheduling repeated tasks).

title: Fix for not showing progressbar on some occasions
message:
Fix for not showing progressbar on some occasions

When caller starts the new task in onExecute callback of existing task, then the "old" progressbar was hidden after new task started (which showed "new" progressbar), and thus the old callback hid the "new" progressbar.

Now onExecute callback is started at the end of the method which solves this problem.

title: Remove almost all uses of getApplicationContext()

Remove almost all uses of getApplicationContext()

Avoid using getApplicationContext() on that many places, where it's not needed. Use getApplicationContext() when you're remembering it (assigning to class attribute), but when giving as method parameter feel free to give classic Context. Only at the end (when assigning) use getApplicationContext() from that given one.

title: Fix doing network requests from more threads
message:
Fix doing network requests from more threads

With this commit is doRequest method synchronized which means it will block other threads until return which means request and response will be done together. This way only one request will be sent to server at once.
Without it it caused getting wrong responses to wrong requests which resulted in crashes...

title: Fix CallbackTask to notify only exceptions
message:
Fix CallbackTask to notify only exceptions

Before this commit it notified as errors also when result was false, which is not an error but it could be standard state (e.g. all data are fresh...)

message: Fix login progress message

title: Fix slow communication with server and enable persistentConnection again
message:
Fix slow communication with server and enable persistentConnection again

We were waiting for </com> element at end of the message, but server sometimes sent shorter tag <com ... /> which resulted in waiting until server's timeout. With this commit we're waiting only for any ">" at the end which could be potentially problem if server send \n not only at the end of <com> tag, but after any other tag because we wouldn't load whole message...

title: Perform alternative login when BlackBerry is detected
message:
Perform alternative login when BlackBerry is detected

When BlackBerry is detected, the BlackBerryLoginActivity
is used to obtain the Google Token and Controller.assignToken()
is called to initialize user data in the application.

title: Implement Controller.assignToken(), alternative to login()
message:
Implement Controller.assignToken(), alternative to login()

When login is not performed by the standard Google way,
we obtain the token by another channel. This is the case
of BlackBerryLoginActivity. So, we start with token only
and obtain Google User Info from the server.

No persistence of user data is implemented at the moment.
I would be glad to have it but the spagetti code of the
login and doLogin functions is quite unreadable to do
it easily. It is not clear when/how to check the persistable
storage before the actual login... To be done later.

title: Add BlackBerryLoginActivity to cover the web login
message:
Add BlackBerryLoginActivity to cover the web login

The activity should be probably renamed to WebLoginActivity.
It is not very complete but works. Any connection problems
are not tested and probably not very well handled (I do not
know how to do it properly).

The login data are logged using Log.d which may leak some
sensitive information (should be switched off later).

Principle:

* start WebView and load Google login page
* user inserts its credentials and logs into his/her account
* then the user accepts the application's access (done when errorCode == -2)
* we now obtain the token by FinishLoginTask and provide it to
  the calling activity as data identified by "google.token" string
